  "prompt": "Is T-fal cookware oven safe?",
  "response": "Whether or not a T-fal pan is oven safe depends on the specific line and the materials it's made of. Here's a general guide:\n\n*   **Most T-fal cookware is oven safe to some degree.**\n*   **Handles:** The biggest factor is the handles. Bakelite handles (a type of plastic) generally have a lower oven-safe temperature (often around 350\u00b0F or 175\u00b0C). Stainless steel handles are usually oven-safe to higher temperatures.\n*   **Nonstick coating:** The nonstick coating itself is typically oven-safe up to a certain temperature, but exceeding that temperature can damage it and release potentially harmful fumes.\n*   **Glass lids:** Glass lids may or may not be oven-safe, and they usually have a lower temperature limit than the pans themselves.\n\n**To find the specific oven-safe temperature for your T-fal cookware, you should:**\n\n1.  **Check the bottom of the pan:** Many T-fal pans have the oven-safe temperature stamped on the bottom.\n2.  **Consult the owner's manual or packaging:** This is the most reliable source of information. If you've lost the manual, you might be able to find it on the T-fal website.\n3.  **Visit the T-fal website:** Search for your specific pan model on the T-fal website. The product description should list the oven-safe temperature.\n4.  **Contact T-fal customer support:** If you can't find the information elsewhere, contact T-fal directly.\n\n**General guidelines (but always verify with your specific product's information):**\n\n*   **T-fal pans with Bakelite handles:** Usually oven-safe up to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C).\n*   **T-fal pans with stainless steel handles:** Often oven-safe to higher temperatures, such as 400\u00b0F to 500\u00b0F (200\u00b0C to 260\u00b0C).\n*   **T-fal glass lids:** May only be oven-safe to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C) or not at all.\n\n**Important Safety Considerations:**\n\n*   **Always use oven mitts or pot holders** when handling hot cookware.\n*   **Never broil with T-fal nonstick cookware,** as the high heat can damage the nonstick coating.\n*   **Avoid sudden temperature changes,** which can warp the pan. Don't take a cold pan and immediately put it into a hot oven.\n*   **Do not overheat empty cookware**, this can damage the non-stick coating and potentially release harmful fumes.\n\nIn summary, while many T-fal pans are oven-safe, **you must check the specifications for your specific product to determine the safe temperature limit.** Exceeding the recommended temperature can damage the pan and potentially release harmful chemicals.\n",
